  "prompt": "When a parking sign says 2-hour parking from 8 to 5 on Monday-Friday, what does it mean for the remainder of the time?",
  "response": "When a parking sign specifies 2-hour parking from 8 AM to 5 PM on Monday through Friday, it typically means that:\n\n1. During those hours and days, parking is limited to 2 hours.\n2. Outside of those hours and days (nights, weekends, and holidays), there are usually no time restrictions on parking.\n\nSo, for example:\n- Evenings after 5 PM: No parking time limit\n- Nights: No parking time limit\n- Weekends: No parking time limit\n- Holidays: No parking time limit\n\nHowever, always check the specific sign or local parking regulations, as rules can vary by location.",
